Trim the @green beans{150%g} then chop into thirds.

Roughly chop the @flat leaf parsley{1%bunch} (stalks and all). Zest half the @lemon{1}.

Peel and grate the @garlic clove{1} (or use a #garlic press{}).

Pour the boiling @water{300%ml} into a #measuring jug{}. Add the @chicken stock powder{1/2%tbsp} and stir to dissolve.

== Bulgur ==

Heat a splash of @oil{} in a large #saucepan{} over medium-high heat.

Add the green beans, stir and cook for ~{3%minutes} then add half the garlic, stir and cook for another minute.

Add the @bulgur wheat{150%g} and stock. Bring back to the boil cook for ~{1%minute}, cover with a #lid{}, then remove from the heat. Leave for ~{10%minutes}.

== Chicken ==

Pop the @diced chicken breast{260%g} onto a #plate{}. Season with @salt{}.

Drizzle on a splash of @oil{} and sprinkle over the @shawarma spice mix{1}.

Rub the seasonings into the chicken.

> IMPORTANT: Remember to wash your hands and equipment after handling raw meat.

Heat a #frying pan{} over medium-high heat (no oil). When the pan is hot, add the chicken and brown for ~{2%minutes} on each side.

Lower the heat to medium and cook, turning occasionally, ~{8-10%minutes}.

> IMPORTANT: The chicken is cooked when it is no longer pink in the middle.

Once the chicken is cooked, add the remaining garlic and cook for another minute.

Remove from the heat, stir in half the parsley and squeeze on half the lemon juice to taste.

== To Serve ==

When the bulgur is cooked, stir in the lemon zest and the remaining parsley.

Season to taste with lemon juice, @salt{} and @ground black pepper{}.

Share between your plates and top with the chicken.

Finish with a dollop of @greek style natural yoghurt{100%g}. ENJOY!